{
  "texts": [
    "Tondeur et al. [15] indicate a significant disparity in teachers' digital competencies, influenced by contextual and personal factors.",
    "Furthermore, many teachers' digital training focuses on the use of technologies for teaching rather than for research.",
    "This means that although teachers may be trained in using digital tools for instruction and classroom management, they may lack the necessary competencies to conduct high-quality research using these tools [12].",
    "According to Mishra and Koehler [16], effective integration of technology in education requires a balanced approach that encompasses both teaching and research.",
    "Although significant efforts have been made to improve teachers' digital training, the lack of investigative competencies remains a challenge."
  ]
}